# HTML Media
--What is a real world use case for the alt attribute being used in a website?
  The 'alt' attribute in HTML is used to provide alternative text for images.
  The primary purpose is to improve the accessibility of a website for users who cannot see the images.

--How can you improve accessibility of images in an HTML document?
   Provide a concise and descriptive text alternative for each image using the 'alt' attribute. 
  use Use semantic HTML, like <figure> and <figcaption> to provide additional context and description
  Ensure good contrast and avoid text within images.

Provide an example of when the figure element would be useful in an HTML document.
<figure>
  <img src="starry-night.jpg" alt="Starry Night by Vincent van Gogh">
  <figcaption>The iconic painting "Starry Night" by Vincent van Gogh.</figcaption>
</figure>
Describe the difference between a gif image and an svg image, pretend you are explaining to an elder in your community.
  Graphics Interchange Format and Scalable Vector Graphics are types of image formats.
  GIF are a series of pictures are shown quickly to make a simple animation like a flipbook.
   is like a set of instructions for drawing pictures.GIF is good for fun animations And SVG are great for logos.
What image type would you use to display a screenshot on your website and why?
  When displaying a screenshot on a website, it's often best to use a PNG (Portable Network Graphics) image
   it retains high quality and sharpness.

